The paper deals with communication complexity and polynomial techniques for analyzing functions, which are topics typically found in the categories of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of duality and the study of discrepancy suggest a connection to topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper also touches on spectral norms and machine learning, which are relevant to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
